JJJ and their role in the H-Doujin community, especially with the annoying sis series, reminds me a lot of ONE's role in the mangaka community with the One Punch Man webcomic. The art on both stories is rough compared to the wider community, but the story is still written well and is hilarious and scenes have more than enough oomph for them to be badass/hot (Badass for OPM, Hot in Annoying Sis).

The style of art and the overall quality of the drawings doesn't have to matter if you can capture the essence of a hot, brother-sister story that's both witty, cute, and entertaining.

10/10, hoping one day that Yusuke Murata also reads hentai and decides to adapt this to manga, then Annoying Sis really could be the "One Punch Man of h-doujins".
